<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A47D785A-6A61-454A-B77A-E8D10016DB1C" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A47D785A-6A61-454A-B77A-E8D10016DB1C" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Lighter areas every 50-70 cm</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-50B00AD6-0A38-41AB-B3CF-DCE2951AFA8A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-AA5EFB49-0298-4500-9038-71A394C600A1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-60F69794-8651-41C7-A3B5-86CAF7F7F254-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-60F69794-8651-41C7-A3B5-86CAF7F7F254-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-9C3461C6-DA01-4891-8122-14C6C4F10B28" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1E4FE56E-4E91-41D4-BC1E-19F7618C83F0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1E4FE56E-4E91-41D4-BC1E-19F7618C83F0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Horizontal lighter area’s every 50 to 70 cm 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Light area’s are visible over complete width of the image 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Area’s located at swath boundaries 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Distance is in depended of used print mode 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Only visible when using Tight-winding / Unlocked Tension bar 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-D7130B4E-8D30-4FD8-B457-DD019A5BD0E3" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional Logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "> Media step accuracy</i> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><fig id="GUID-67A69176-A12D-40D7-AB02-FAB2CB6021D5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A62AC801-5936-4326-9F79-B1B301D75EE7-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A62AC801-5936-4326-9F79-B1B301D75EE7-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The chart above is example to the “Media step accuracy”-logging. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> As can be seen there is a repeating pattern every 60 cm in the shape of a tailfin. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This pattern is also mirrored between the left (blue line) and the right (orange line) of the print.
</p></section><section id="GUID-B85770FB-B0D7-4A54-B32C-CD747506951B" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM-triggers available. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><p class="- topic/p ">Use the correct profile for the used media which can be downloaded from: 
<xref href="https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/</xref>. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">Always use the correct profiles which can be downloaded from 
<xref href="https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/</xref>. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">In case weak media is used, the tension bar is needed to pull the media through the printer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the tension bar is at is lowest position the winder starts winding and pulls the tension bar back up. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">During this process the pulling force on the media slightly increases. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If media is not stretchable enough this will result in an temporary increase of the media step which leads to a lighter area on the print. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The usage of the tension bar is described in 
<xref keyref="19FUNCEXPLANATIONWINDINGmode" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1E95BDBB-A73F-49E7-9E2F-24A7C496890D.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="reference"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 19 Explanation Winding modes and when to use?>19 Explanation Winding modes and when to use</xref>. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
